github-rename-default-branch - GitHub Default Branch Renamer

USAGE:
    github-rename-default-branch <from-branch> <to-branch>

DESCRIPTION:
    Rename default branch for all GitHub repositories. Clones each repo,
    renames the branch, pushes changes, sets new default, and deletes old branch.

ARGUMENTS:
    from-branch
        Current default branch name (e.g., master)

    to-branch
        New default branch name (e.g., main)

NOTE:
    Processes up to 1000 repositories. Requires GitHub authentication.

EXAMPLES:
    github-rename-default-branch master main
    github-rename-default-branch master develop
